                    "errata": {
                      "alt": "2.0",
                      "aonid": 216,
                      "game-obj": "Sources",
                      "name": "2.0",
                      "type": "link"
                    },
                    "link": {
                      "alt": "Player Core pg. 282",
                      "aonid": 216,
                      "game-obj": "Sources",
                      "name": "Player Core pg. 282",
                      "type": "link"
                    },
                    "name": "Player Core",
                    "page": 282,
                    "type": "source"
                  }
                ],
                "text": "The multiple attack penalty you take with this weapon on the second attack on your turn is \u20134 instead of \u20135, and \u20138 instead of \u201310 on the third and subsequent attacks in the turn.",
                "type": "trait"
              },
              {
                "alternate_link": {
                  "alternate_type": "legacy",
                  "aonid": 179,
                  "game-obj": "Traits",
                  "type": "alternate_link"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "game-id": "6a57956799f3d30121d529e48f12904c",
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "name": "Finesse",
                "sources": [
                  {
                    "errata": {
                      "alt": "2.0",
                      "aonid": 216,
                      "game-obj": "Sources",
                      "name": "2.0",
                      "type": "link"
                    },
                    "link": {
                      "alt": "Player Core pg. 282",
                      "aonid": 216,
                      "game-obj": "Sources",
                      "name": "Player Core pg. 282",
                      "type": "link"
                    },
                    "name": "Player Core",
                    "page": 282,
                    "type": "source"
                  }
                ],
                "text": "You can use your Dexterity modifier instead of your Strength modifier on attack rolls using this melee weapon. You still calculate damage using Strength.",
                "type": "trait"
              },
              {
                "edition": "remastered",
                "game-id": "2f3295840cd39bc5926fa41d78f26885",
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "links": [
                  {
                    "alt": "unholy",
                    "aonid": 521,
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "name": "unholy",
                    "type": "link"
                  }
                ],
                "name": "Holy",
                "sources": [
                  {
                    "errata": {
                      "alt": "2.0",
                      "aonid": 216,
                      "game-obj": "Sources",
                      "name": "2.0",
                      "type": "link"
                    },
                    "link": {
                      "alt": "Player Core pg. 457",
                      "aonid": 216,
                      "game-obj": "Sources",
                      "name": "Player Core pg. 457",
                      "type": "link"
                    },
                    "name": "Player Core",
                    "page": 457,
                    "type": "source"
                  }
                ],
                "text": "Effects with the holy trait are tied to powerful magical forces of benevolence and virtue. They often have stronger effects on unholy creatures. Creatures with this trait are strongly devoted to holy causes and often have weakness to unholy. If a creature with weakness to holy uses a holy item or effect, it takes damage from its weakness.",
                "type": "trait"
              },
              {
                "alternate_link": {
                  "alternate_type": "legacy",
                  "aonid": 103,
                  "game-obj": "Traits",
                  "type": "alternate_link"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "game-id": "15e2d048ce93e7b648064b09972535bc",
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "name": "Magical",
                "sources": [
                  {
                    "errata": {
                      "alt": "2.0",
                      "aonid": 216,
                      "game-obj": "Sources",
                      "name": "2.0",
                      "type": "link"
                    },
                    "link": {
                      "alt": "Player Core pg. 458",
                      "aonid": 216,
                      "game-obj": "Sources",
                      "name": "Player Core pg. 458",
                      "type": "link"
                    },
                    "name": "Player Core",
                    "page": 458,
                    "type": "source"
                  }
                ],
                "text": "Something with the magical trait is imbued with magical energies not tied to a specific tradition of magic. Some items or effects are closely tied to a particular tradition of magic. In these cases, the item has the arcane, divine, occult, or primal trait instead of the magical trait. Any of these traits indicate that the item is magical.",
                "type": "trait"
              }
            ],
